Package: nfa-linux
Version: 1.0.0
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libgtk-3-0 (>= 3.22), libwebkit2gtk-4.1-0 (>= 2.40), libpcap0.8
Recommends: wireshark-common
Suggests: tshark
Maintainer: NFA-Linux Team <team@nfa-linux.io>
Homepage: https://github.com/cvalentine99/NFA-Linux-
Description: Network Forensics Analyzer - Next Generation Packet Analysis
 NFA-Linux is a high-performance network forensics analyzer designed for
 digital forensics and incident response (DFIR) professionals. It provides
 real-time packet capture, protocol analysis, and threat detection.
 .
 Key Features:
  - 10Gbps packet capture with AF_XDP/eBPF
  - JA3/JA4 TLS fingerprinting
  - ML-based anomaly detection
  - CASE/UCO evidence export
  - 3D network topology visualization
  - File carving and extraction
 .
 This package includes the desktop GUI application built with Wails.
 .
 Supported on Ubuntu 22.04+ and Debian 12+.
